{
  "stem": "22869.3",
  "chunk_idx": 13,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "I still remember, his name was Mr.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "Mueller.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "He was an elderly gentleman, and they introduced him that he is a brick layer master.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "Master bricklayer.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "And he's looking for some young people whom he wants to train and give them schooling in brick laying.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So they tell us that whoever will volunteer will have a chance to be inside a building the whole day, [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] and they will teach us how to become masters in brick laying.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So I said, it's better than going out to work.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So I volunteered.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And my brother-- my middle brother-- also volunteered.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And they took us away from Birkenau to Auschwitz, to the main camp now.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And there, they erected in one of the blocks on the third floor a place as today as you would picture a basement in somebody's house, where they brought a lot of bricks-- dry bricks, no mortar-- and this civilian came in every day to give us lectures on how you're supposed to lay bricks.",
      "word_count": 55
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Without any cement, just dry.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "He showed how to make corners, how to make walls, and how to keep them straight, and how to pull a string across, and how to use a [NON-ENGLISH], a level-- which is mean.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And-- but we picked up a little strength.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "It was-- it was like a relief from what we were going through up until now-- I mean, not a comparison.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "First of all, in the place of work, you didn't get beat anymore.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Because this German civilian-- he didn't-- he might have yelled at us, but he did not beat anybody.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And we were no-- under no SS guard supervision inside the block.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "So it was like going from-- from hell to paradise all of a sudden.",
      "word_count": 14
    }
  ],
